<HEADLINE>
EDUCATION MINISTER TO ATTEND WORLD EDUCATION MEETING IN ENGLAND
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  Jan.  4  (CNA) 01/04/07  16:40:21 (By Luis Huang)
</P>
<P>
Education Minister Tu Cheng-sheng is scheduled to head for the
United Kingdom Jan. 6 to attend an international meeting of
education ministers, an official with the Ministry of Education
said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, ministers of education from over 40
countries around the world will take part in the conference
slated for Jan. 8-10.
</P>
<P>
Asked whether China will be among the 40 participant nations, the
official said he is not sure whether the Chinese minister of
education will also attend the upcoming meeting.
</P>
<P>
Following the three-day conference, Tu is scheduled to visit the
London School of Economics and Political Science on the afternoon
of Jan. 10 to deliver a speech on the future of Taiwan, the
official said.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by Ho Chuo-fei, director general of the Department of
Physical Education, the minister of education will travel to
Italy Jan. 11 to take part in an executive meeting of the
International University Sports Federation (FISU), during which
they will help the Kaoshiung City government's bid for the right
to host the 2011 Summer Universiade.
</P>
<P>
Kaohsiung has been selected by the FISU as one of the five
official candidate cities to host the 2011 event. The other four
candidates are Shenzhen in China, Kazan in Russia, Poznan in
Poland and Murcia in Spain.
</P>
